@bsidhom The reason for that test failure is that Flink doesn't register source operators with the execution environment because typically you don't have a pipeline with only sources. You can manually do that by adding this after creating the source in `BoundedReadSourceTranslator.translateNode(...)`:
```
context.getExecutionEnvironment().addOperator(source.getTransformation());
```

The reason for this seems to be that this code no longer creates a dummy par do: https://github.com/apache/beam/blob/fa61ed17424083fa53b8aa8e70908fb6194ad4ad/runners/flink/src/main/java/org/apache/beam/runners/flink/FlinkStreamingPipelineTranslator.java#L68

@pawel-kaczmarczyk could you please rebase to the latest master.
I added some changes including upgrading the version of Kinesis in the last days and I would like to be sure that everything works as expected.
For info we are preparing a PR for the Write transform (if everything goes as expected we will open the PR next week) and that I hope you, @jkff and/or @rtshadow can help us to review it. Thanks
